TITLE: U.S. explores working with India to increase economic competition against China, says Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo
SUMMARY: Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo says a collaboration between the U.S. and India can compete with the Chinese semiconductor monopoly.

TITLE: Ukraine's Zelenskyy expected to ask for more aid from European leaders in Brussels trip
SUMMARY: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy will be in Brussels to ask EU lawmakers and leaders for more support as Russia's invasion of Ukraine drags on.

TITLE: Biden's State of the Union may not help potential 2024 election bid against Trump, experts say
SUMMARY: Biden has yet to confirm his plans for the next election cycle, but he's expected to make a decision soon, according to various news outlets.

TITLE: Zelenskyy asks Europe for more aid, calls Russia the 'biggest anti-European force' in modern world
SUMMARY: The president's trip comes at a critical point for Ukraine, with authorities expecting a large-scale offensive by Russia.

TITLE: Angry senators grill Pentagon officials over Chinese spy balloon response
SUMMARY: Senators were visibly angry as they pressed Pentagon officials on when they learned of the Chinese spy balloon, and why they waited so long to shoot it down.

TITLE: FBI investigating Chinese spy balloon, but much of the evidence is still under water
SUMMARY: The spy balloon is believed to be just latest of Chinese surveillance airships that crossed air spaces of the U.S. and dozens of other countries.

TITLE: Rep. Angie Craig assaulted in apartment building elevator, her office says
SUMMARY: There is currently "no evidence" that the incident against Craig, the first openly LGBT member of Congress from her state, was "politically motivated."

TITLE: GOP voters pick DeSantis over Trump in hypothetical head-to-head matchup for 2024 presidential nomination, poll shows
SUMMARY: Trump, who lost to President Joe Biden in 2020, is still a main contender for the 2024 race, Monmouth University's latest survey showed.

TITLE: Biden's billionaire tax is 'dead on arrival' in Congress, top Wall Street backers and Democratic strategists say
SUMMARY: Biden's billionaire tax would subject households with a net worth above $100 million to pay a minimum annual tax of 20% on gains of their "tradable assets."

SUMMARY: Donald Trump pressured his vice president, Mike Pence, to refuse to certify state election results that gave President Joe Biden his margin of victory in 2020.

TITLE: Rep. George Santos was charged with theft in since-dismissed 2017 dog breeder case
SUMMARY: Santos has been caught under a mountain of lies, scandals and investigations since shortly after he won his New York congressional race.

TITLE: Trump special counsel subpoenas former VP Mike Pence in Jan. 6 probe
SUMMARY: Donald Trump pressured his vice president, Mike Pence, to refuse to certify state election results that gave President Joe Biden his margin of victory in 2020.

TITLE: FBI is searching home of Mike Pence for more classified documents
SUMMARY: The search was planned to take place today following negotiations between the Just Department and Pence's lawyers.

TITLE: National Archives, Smithsonian museum sued after visitors told to remove 'pro-life' clothing
SUMMARY: The National Archives is apologizing after a lawsuit accused its security guards of telling visitors to cover up clothes with 'pro-life' messages.

TITLE: Judge extends deadline in lawsuit seeking to pull abortion pill mifepristone from U.S. until Feb. 24
SUMMARY: The abortion rights group NARAL Pro-Choice America, in an analysis published Friday, said 40 million women could lose access to the abortion pill.

TITLE: Top House Republicans scrutinize SEC investigation of failed crypto exchange FTX
SUMMARY: GOP leaders in the House Financial Services Committee requested communications between the SEC and the DOJ on the arrest of former FTX CEO Sam Bankman-Fried.

TITLE: SEC weighs making 'adjustments' to controversial climate risk disclosure rule, Chairman Gensler says
SUMMARY: SEC chair Gensler, said politics did not come into play in the agency's decision to modify its controversial climate risk disclosure rule.

TITLE: U.S. sanctions six Chinese tech companies for supporting spy balloon programs
SUMMARY: The sanctions came just hours after an American military F-22 shot down the second "high altitude object" to enter U.S. airspace in the past week.

SUMMARY: The object was destroyed by a missile from an F-22 fighter plane off the northeastern coast of Alaska.

TITLE: Republicans back lawsuit to overturn FDA approval of abortion pill and pull the medication from U.S. market
SUMMARY: The 22 attorneys general argued the attempt to pull the abortion pill from the U.S. market would have "devastating consequences" for women.

TITLE: FBI finds another classified document in search of Mike Pence's home, his spokesman says
SUMMARY: The search of Pence's home came after classified documents were found at President Joe Biden's home in Delaware.

TITLE: U.S. shoots down a fourth high-altitude object as lawmakers demand more information
SUMMARY: Members of Congress say they have not been briefed about four high-altitude objects downed in the airspace above the U.S. and Canada.

TITLE: Parts of Trump Georgia grand jury report on election meddling to be released this week
SUMMARY: The grand jury's investigation included looking at the actions of former President Donald Trump and his allies.

TITLE: White House defends shooting down three aerial objects, despite not knowing who launched them or why
SUMMARY: The White House on Monday said it doesn't yet know what the aerial objects are that were shot down this weekend, who owns them or their purpose.
